cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.HC 

The paper discusses the communication between humans and AI systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of AI systems and optimization techniques also suggests the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The development of a model based on a conditional convolutional autoencoder (CCAE) indicates the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the investigation of how humans can adjust their behavior to improve communication efficiency suggests the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
